cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multiple mobile agents and their interactions in a shared environment. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses strategies for allocating vertices to be occupied by the team of defenders. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is relevant as the paper describes the asymmetric goals of the two teams and the adversarial nature of the scenario. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of a visibility graph to model communication between vertices. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with mobile agents moving in a graph-based environment.
